Posted: Sat May 05, 2012 12:11 pm
Just got back from a short trip to Florida. When we were there it was tough to tell if the mixing valve on the kitchen tap was malfunctioning, or if the "cold water" was just poorly named.Returned home to upstate NY yesterday, and this morning I was so struck by the difference that I grabbed a kitchen thermometer. My cold tap water is running around 52f. I have a cheap infrared meter that I'll try later today to see if it agrees, but my hands tell me that it is at least close.So:Your cold water tap. Is it just plain labeled wrong, or does it deliver?Actual reading welcome as are other general comments regarding water quality. When we vacation we use store bought water for drinking and coffee, but tap water for ice and cooking. At home our tap water is municipal, but good to drink; it comes from a local lake not from hundreds of miles away.Yesterday in the airport my wife bought a bottle of water (in Florida) that claimed to be NYC water. It is fair to say that the water in Manhatten is good; but as far as I know it comes a fair distance to get there, mostly from the Adirondacks.
