I'm on Indianapolis municipal water, and it's cool in the summer (and will get colder if you let it run) and can be downright frigid in the winter.I actually kind of like being on city water. It tastes fine*, so it saves me $$ because I can just fill up gallon jugs straight from the tap and put them in the fridge to get cold. No need to buy a filter or buy bottled water or anything.* - We do have a couple of weeks every year (usually either early in the summer or late in the summer) when the water tastes like catfish piss. I'm told that it's due to low water levels in the reservoir(s).
