I rented a shack for a few years ("house" or even "cottage" would be too generous, but the price was right ) where the pipes feeding the kitchen sink ran on the outside of the wall, on the wall facing due west. In the afternoons the first 30 seconds of water out of the cold tap would be blazing hot, even dangerously so.Around here in "Climate Best by Government Test" the climate's pretty temperate, and the water out of the tap is accordingly cool but not cold.
