Posted: Mon May 07, 2012 10:01 am
Once you get the hot water out of the lines there's a difference between hot and cold. Until then, there isn't much of a difference though. Cold runs around 70 and I think the hot water heater is set to 120 or there abouts. In our guest house/rec room, you have to let the water run for ~15 seconds before you can even consider to use it on either setting as all the piping is run along the rafters and down a west wall. Eventually, you'll get cool water once it starts drawing fresh water from the well, but the well is only 35-40 feet down so it isn't *that* cool. If you need to cool off, that's what the swimming pool is for. (Once you've checked it for gators and cotton mouths first) AmigaPhreak
